Note:
Runa Standard Library: Core SQL Operations Module

This module provides comprehensive SQL query building, execution, and result handling
capabilities for the Runa database ecosystem. It serves as the foundation for all
SQL-based database drivers and provides a type-safe, composable query builder
with support for complex joins, subqueries, transactions, and prepared statements.

Key Features:
- Type-safe SQL query builder with method chaining
- Comprehensive support for SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE operations
- Advanced JOIN operations (INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, FULL OUTER, CROSS)
- Subquery and CTE (Common Table Expression) support
- Transaction management with rollback and commit
- Prepared statement generation and parameter binding
- Result set handling with type conversion
- SQL injection prevention through parameterization
- Database-agnostic SQL generation with dialect support
- Connection management and query execution

Architecture:
Provides a layered SQL abstraction with high-level query builders for common operations,
mid-level SQL AST manipulation for complex queries, and low-level parameter binding
and result set processing for performance-critical applications.
:End Note

Import "collections/list" as list_utils
Import "collections/dict" as dict_utils
Import "string/format" as string_utils
Import "datetime/core" as datetime_core

Note: Core SQL Types

Type SQLDialect is Enumeration with:
    postgresql
    mysql
    sqlite
    mariadb
    oracle
    sqlserver
    generic

Type SQLDataType is Enumeration with:
    integer
    bigint
    varchar
    text
    boolean
    decimal
    float_type
    double_type
    date
    datetime
    timestamp
    binary
    json_type
    uuid_type

Type JoinType is Enumeration with:
    inner_join
    left_join
    right_join
    full_outer_join
    cross_join

Type OrderDirection is Enumeration with:
    ascending
    descending

Type QueryType is Enumeration with:
    select_query
    insert_query
    update_query
    delete_query
    create_table_query
    drop_table_query
    alter_table_query

Type SQLConnection is Dictionary with:
    connection_id as String
    database_url as String
    dialect as SQLDialect
    is_connected as Boolean
    transaction_level as Integer
    autocommit as Boolean
    connection_metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type SQLResult is Union with:
    QuerySuccess with:
        rows as List[Dictionary[String, Any]]
        affected_rows as Integer
        execution_time_ms as Integer
        metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    QueryError with:
        error as SQLError
        query as Optional[String]
        parameters as Optional[List[Any]]

Type SQLError is Dictionary with:
    error_code as String
    message as String
    sql_state as Optional[String]
    query as Optional[String]
    position as Optional[Integer]

Type PreparedStatement is Dictionary with:
    statement_id as String
    sql_query as String
    parameter_count as Integer
    parameter_types as List[SQLDataType]
    is_prepared as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type QueryBuilder is Dictionary with:
    query_type as QueryType
    table_name as Optional[String]
    columns as List[String]
    where_conditions as List[WhereCondition]
    join_clauses as List[JoinClause]
    order_by_clauses as List[OrderByClause]
    group_by_columns as List[String]
    having_conditions as List[WhereCondition]
    limit_count as Optional[Integer]
    offset_count as Optional[Integer]
    subqueries as List[SubQuery]
    parameters as List[SQLParameter]
    dialect as SQLDialect

Type WhereCondition is Dictionary with:
    column as String
    operator as String
    value as Any
    logical_operator as String
    is_parameterized as Boolean

Type JoinClause is Dictionary with:
    join_type as JoinType
    table_name as String
    table_alias as Optional[String]
    on_condition as String
    is_subquery as Boolean

Type OrderByClause is Dictionary with:
    column as String
    direction as OrderDirection
    nulls_first as Boolean

Type SubQuery is Dictionary with:
    subquery_id as String
    sql_query as String
    alias as String
    parameters as List[SQLParameter]

Type SQLParameter is Dictionary with:
    parameter_name as String
    value as Any
    data_type as SQLDataType
    position as Integer

Note: Query Builder Implementation

Process called "create_query_builder" that takes dialect as Optional[SQLDialect] returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Create a new SQL query builder instance
    Try:
        Let builder_dialect be dialect if dialect is not None else SQLDialect.generic
        
        Return QueryBuilder with:
            query_type as QueryType.select_query
            table_name as None
            columns as empty list
            where_conditions as empty list
            join_clauses as empty list
            order_by_clauses as empty list
            group_by_columns as empty list
            having_conditions as empty list
            limit_count as None
            offset_count as None
            subqueries as empty list
            parameters as empty list
            dialect as builder_dialect
    
    Catch error:
        Return QueryBuilder with:
            query_type as QueryType.select_query
            table_name as None
            columns as empty list
            where_conditions as empty list
            join_clauses as empty list
            order_by_clauses as empty list
            group_by_columns as empty list
            having_conditions as empty list
            limit_count as None
            offset_count as None
            subqueries as empty list
            parameters as empty list
            dialect as SQLDialect.generic

Process called "select_from" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and table as String returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Set the table name for SELECT query
    Try:
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Set updated_builder.query_type to QueryType.select_query
        Set updated_builder.table_name to Some with value as table
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "select_columns" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and columns as List[String] returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Set the columns to select
    Try:
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Set updated_builder.columns to columns
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "where_equals" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and column as String and value as Any returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add WHERE column = value condition
    Try:
        Let condition be WhereCondition with:
            column as column
            operator as "="
            value as value
            logical_operator as determine_logical_operator with conditions as builder.where_conditions
            is_parameterized as true
        
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Add condition to updated_builder.where_conditions
        
        Let parameter be SQLParameter with:
            parameter_name as generate_parameter_name with position as length of updated_builder.parameters
            value as value
            data_type as infer_sql_data_type with value as value
            position as length of updated_builder.parameters
        
        Add parameter to updated_builder.parameters
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "where_in" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and column as String and values as List[Any] returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add WHERE column IN (values) condition
    Try:
        Let in_values_string be build_in_clause_values with values as values and builder as builder
        
        Let condition be WhereCondition with:
            column as column
            operator as "IN"
            value as in_values_string
            logical_operator as determine_logical_operator with conditions as builder.where_conditions
            is_parameterized as true
        
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Add condition to updated_builder.where_conditions
        
        Note: Add parameters for each value in the IN clause
        For each value in values:
            Let parameter be SQLParameter with:
                parameter_name as generate_parameter_name with position as length of updated_builder.parameters
                value as value
                data_type as infer_sql_data_type with value as value
                position as length of updated_builder.parameters
            
            Add parameter to updated_builder.parameters
        
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "where_like" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and column as String and pattern as String returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add WHERE column LIKE pattern condition
    Try:
        Let condition be WhereCondition with:
            column as column
            operator as "LIKE"
            value as pattern
            logical_operator as determine_logical_operator with conditions as builder.where_conditions
            is_parameterized as true
        
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Add condition to updated_builder.where_conditions
        
        Let parameter be SQLParameter with:
            parameter_name as generate_parameter_name with position as length of updated_builder.parameters
            value as pattern
            data_type as SQLDataType.varchar
            position as length of updated_builder.parameters
        
        Add parameter to updated_builder.parameters
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "where_between" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and column as String and start_value as Any and end_value as Any returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add WHERE column BETWEEN start_value AND end_value condition
    Try:
        Let between_expression be "BETWEEN " plus generate_parameter_placeholder with dialect as builder.dialect and position as length of builder.parameters
        Set between_expression to between_expression plus " AND " plus generate_parameter_placeholder with dialect as builder.dialect and position as (length of builder.parameters plus 1)
        
        Let condition be WhereCondition with:
            column as column
            operator as between_expression
            value as ""
            logical_operator as determine_logical_operator with conditions as builder.where_conditions
            is_parameterized as true
        
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Add condition to updated_builder.where_conditions
        
        Note: Add parameters for start and end values
        Let start_parameter be SQLParameter with:
            parameter_name as generate_parameter_name with position as length of updated_builder.parameters
            value as start_value
            data_type as infer_sql_data_type with value as start_value
            position as length of updated_builder.parameters
        Add start_parameter to updated_builder.parameters
        
        Let end_parameter be SQLParameter with:
            parameter_name as generate_parameter_name with position as length of updated_builder.parameters
            value as end_value
            data_type as infer_sql_data_type with value as end_value
            position as length of updated_builder.parameters
        Add end_parameter to updated_builder.parameters
        
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "inner_join" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and table as String and on_condition as String returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add INNER JOIN clause
    Try:
        Let join_clause be JoinClause with:
            join_type as JoinType.inner_join
            table_name as table
            table_alias as None
            on_condition as on_condition
            is_subquery as false
        
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Add join_clause to updated_builder.join_clauses
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "left_join" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and table as String and on_condition as String returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add LEFT JOIN clause
    Try:
        Let join_clause be JoinClause with:
            join_type as JoinType.left_join
            table_name as table
            table_alias as None
            on_condition as on_condition
            is_subquery as false
        
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Add join_clause to updated_builder.join_clauses
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "order_by" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and column as String and direction as Optional[OrderDirection] returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add ORDER BY clause
    Try:
        Let sort_direction be direction if direction is not None else OrderDirection.ascending
        
        Let order_clause be OrderByClause with:
            column as column
            direction as sort_direction
            nulls_first as false
        
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Add order_clause to updated_builder.order_by_clauses
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "group_by" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and columns as List[String] returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add GROUP BY clause
    Try:
        Let updated_builder be builder
        For each column in columns:
            Add column to updated_builder.group_by_columns
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "having" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and condition as String returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add HAVING clause condition
    Try:
        Let having_condition be WhereCondition with:
            column as ""
            operator as ""
            value as condition
            logical_operator as determine_logical_operator with conditions as builder.having_conditions
            is_parameterized as false
        
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Add having_condition to updated_builder.having_conditions
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "limit" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and count as Integer returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add LIMIT clause
    Try:
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Set updated_builder.limit_count to Some with value as count
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Process called "offset" that takes builder as QueryBuilder and count as Integer returns QueryBuilder:
    Note: Add OFFSET clause
    Try:
        Let updated_builder be builder
        Set updated_builder.offset_count to Some with value as count
        Return updated_builder
    
    Catch error:
        Return builder

Note: Query Generation

Process called "build_select_query" that takes builder as QueryBuilder returns String:
    Note: Generate complete SELECT SQL query from builder
    Try:
        Let query be "SELECT "
        
        Note: Build column list
        If length of builder.columns is equal to 0:
            Set query to query plus "*"
        Else:
            Set query to query plus join_strings with strings as builder.columns and separator as ", "
        
        Note: Add FROM clause
        If builder.table_name is not None:
            Set query to query plus " FROM " plus (builder.table_name as String)
        
        Note: Add JOIN clauses
        For each join_clause in builder.join_clauses:
            Let join_sql be build_join_clause with join as join_clause and dialect as builder.dialect
            Set query to query plus " " plus join_sql
        
        Note: Add WHERE clause
        If length of builder.where_conditions is greater than 0:
            Let where_sql be build_where_clause with conditions as builder.where_conditions and dialect as builder.dialect
            Set query to query plus " WHERE " plus where_sql
        
        Note: Add GROUP BY clause
        If length of builder.group_by_columns is greater than 0:
            Set query to query plus " GROUP BY " plus join_strings with strings as builder.group_by_columns and separator as ", "
        
        Note: Add HAVING clause
        If length of builder.having_conditions is greater than 0:
            Let having_sql be build_where_clause with conditions as builder.having_conditions and dialect as builder.dialect
            Set query to query plus " HAVING " plus having_sql
        
        Note: Add ORDER BY clause
        If length of builder.order_by_clauses is greater than 0:
            Let order_sql be build_order_by_clause with clauses as builder.order_by_clauses and dialect as builder.dialect
            Set query to query plus " ORDER BY " plus order_sql
        
        Note: Add LIMIT clause
        If builder.limit_count is not None:
            Set query to query plus build_limit_clause with count as (builder.limit_count as Integer) and dialect as builder.dialect
        
        Note: Add OFFSET clause
        If builder.offset_count is not None:
            Set query to query plus build_offset_clause with count as (builder.offset_count as Integer) and dialect as builder.dialect
        
        Return query
    
    Catch error:
        Return "SELECT 1"

Process called "build_insert_query" that takes table as String and data as Dictionary[String, Any] and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Generate INSERT SQL query
    Try:
        Let columns be get_dictionary_keys with dict as data
        Let values_placeholders be empty list
        
        For i from 0 to (length of columns minus 1):
            Add generate_parameter_placeholder with dialect as dialect and position as i to values_placeholders
        
        Let query be "INSERT INTO " plus table plus " ("
        Set query to query plus join_strings with strings as columns and separator as ", "
        Set query to query plus ") VALUES ("
        Set query to query plus join_strings with strings as values_placeholders and separator as ", "
        Set query to query plus ")"
        
        Return query
    
    Catch error:
        Return "INSERT INTO table VALUES ()"

Process called "build_update_query" that takes table as String and data as Dictionary[String, Any] and where_conditions as List[WhereCondition] and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Generate UPDATE SQL query
    Try:
        Let query be "UPDATE " plus table plus " SET "
        Let set_clauses be empty list
        Let columns be get_dictionary_keys with dict as data
        
        For i from 0 to (length of columns minus 1):
            Let column be columns at index i
            Let placeholder be generate_parameter_placeholder with dialect as dialect and position as i
            Let set_clause be column plus " = " plus placeholder
            Add set_clause to set_clauses
        
        Set query to query plus join_strings with strings as set_clauses and separator as ", "
        
        Note: Add WHERE clause
        If length of where_conditions is greater than 0:
            Let where_sql be build_where_clause with conditions as where_conditions and dialect as dialect
            Set query to query plus " WHERE " plus where_sql
        
        Return query
    
    Catch error:
        Return "UPDATE table SET column = value"

Process called "build_delete_query" that takes table as String and where_conditions as List[WhereCondition] and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Generate DELETE SQL query
    Try:
        Let query be "DELETE FROM " plus table
        
        Note: Add WHERE clause
        If length of where_conditions is greater than 0:
            Let where_sql be build_where_clause with conditions as where_conditions and dialect as dialect
            Set query to query plus " WHERE " plus where_sql
        
        Return query
    
    Catch error:
        Return "DELETE FROM table"

Note: SQL Clause Building

Process called "build_where_clause" that takes conditions as List[WhereCondition] and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Build WHERE clause from conditions
    Try:
        If length of conditions is equal to 0:
            Return ""
        
        Let where_parts be empty list
        
        For each condition in conditions:
            Let condition_sql be build_single_condition with condition as condition and dialect as dialect
            
            Note: Add logical operator for subsequent conditions
            If length of where_parts is greater than 0 and condition.logical_operator is not equal to "":
                Set condition_sql to condition.logical_operator plus " " plus condition_sql
            
            Add condition_sql to where_parts
        
        Return join_strings with strings as where_parts and separator as " "
    
    Catch error:
        Return "1=1"

Process called "build_single_condition" that takes condition as WhereCondition and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Build single WHERE condition
    Try:
        Let column_name be escape_identifier with name as condition.column and dialect as dialect
        
        Match condition.operator:
            When "=":
                If condition.is_parameterized:
                    Let placeholder be generate_parameter_placeholder with dialect as dialect and position as 0
                    Return column_name plus " = " plus placeholder
                Else:
                    Return column_name plus " = " plus format_sql_value with value as condition.value and dialect as dialect
            
            When "IN":
                Return column_name plus " IN (" plus (condition.value as String) plus ")"
            
            When "LIKE":
                If condition.is_parameterized:
                    Let placeholder be generate_parameter_placeholder with dialect as dialect and position as 0
                    Return column_name plus " LIKE " plus placeholder
                Else:
                    Return column_name plus " LIKE " plus format_sql_value with value as condition.value and dialect as dialect
            
            When "IS NULL":
                Return column_name plus " IS NULL"
            
            When "IS NOT NULL":
                Return column_name plus " IS NOT NULL"
            
            Otherwise:
                If condition.operator is not equal to "":
                    Return column_name plus " " plus condition.operator plus " " plus format_sql_value with value as condition.value and dialect as dialect
                Else:
                    Return condition.value as String
    
    Catch error:
        Return "1=1"

Process called "build_join_clause" that takes join as JoinClause and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Build JOIN clause
    Try:
        Let join_type_sql be ""
        Match join.join_type:
            When JoinType.inner_join:
                Set join_type_sql to "INNER JOIN"
            When JoinType.left_join:
                Set join_type_sql to "LEFT JOIN"
            When JoinType.right_join:
                Set join_type_sql to "RIGHT JOIN"
            When JoinType.full_outer_join:
                Set join_type_sql to "FULL OUTER JOIN"
            When JoinType.cross_join:
                Set join_type_sql to "CROSS JOIN"
            Otherwise:
                Set join_type_sql to "INNER JOIN"
        
        Let table_reference be escape_identifier with name as join.table_name and dialect as dialect
        
        If join.table_alias is not None:
            Set table_reference to table_reference plus " AS " plus escape_identifier with name as (join.table_alias as String) and dialect as dialect
        
        If join.join_type is equal to JoinType.cross_join:
            Return join_type_sql plus " " plus table_reference
        Else:
            Return join_type_sql plus " " plus table_reference plus " ON " plus join.on_condition
    
    Catch error:
        Return "INNER JOIN table ON 1=1"

Process called "build_order_by_clause" that takes clauses as List[OrderByClause] and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Build ORDER BY clause
    Try:
        Let order_parts be empty list
        
        For each clause in clauses:
            Let column_name be escape_identifier with name as clause.column and dialect as dialect
            Let direction_sql be ""
            
            Match clause.direction:
                When OrderDirection.ascending:
                    Set direction_sql to "ASC"
                When OrderDirection.descending:
                    Set direction_sql to "DESC"
                Otherwise:
                    Set direction_sql to "ASC"
            
            Let order_part be column_name plus " " plus direction_sql
            
            If clause.nulls_first:
                Set order_part to order_part plus " NULLS FIRST"
            
            Add order_part to order_parts
        
        Return join_strings with strings as order_parts and separator as ", "
    
    Catch error:
        Return "1"

Process called "build_limit_clause" that takes count as Integer and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Build LIMIT clause based on dialect
    Try:
        Match dialect:
            When SQLDialect.sqlserver:
                Return " TOP " plus (count as String)
            When SQLDialect.oracle:
                Return " ROWNUM <= " plus (count as String)
            Otherwise:
                Return " LIMIT " plus (count as String)
    
    Catch error:
        Return " LIMIT 100"

Process called "build_offset_clause" that takes count as Integer and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Build OFFSET clause based on dialect
    Try:
        Match dialect:
            When SQLDialect.sqlserver:
                Return " OFFSET " plus (count as String) plus " ROWS"
            When SQLDialect.mysql:
                Return " OFFSET " plus (count as String)
            When SQLDialect.postgresql:
                Return " OFFSET " plus (count as String)
            When SQLDialect.sqlite:
                Return " OFFSET " plus (count as String)
            Otherwise:
                Return " OFFSET " plus (count as String)
    
    Catch error:
        Return " OFFSET 0"

Note: Parameter and Value Handling

Process called "generate_parameter_placeholder" that takes dialect as SQLDialect and position as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate parameter placeholder based on dialect
    Try:
        Match dialect:
            When SQLDialect.postgresql:
                Return "$" plus ((position plus 1) as String)
            When SQLDialect.mysql:
                Return "?"
            When SQLDialect.sqlite:
                Return "?"
            When SQLDialect.oracle:
                Return ":" plus "param" plus (position as String)
            When SQLDialect.sqlserver:
                Return "@param" plus (position as String)
            Otherwise:
                Return "?"
    
    Catch error:
        Return "?"

Process called "generate_parameter_name" that takes position as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate parameter name for binding
    Try:
        Return "param_" plus (position as String)
    
    Catch error:
        Return "param_0"

Process called "format_sql_value" that takes value as Any and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Format value for SQL based on type
    Try:
        Match value:
            When String:
                Return "'" plus escape_sql_string with text as (value as String) and dialect as dialect plus "'"
            When Integer:
                Return value as String
            When Float:
                Return value as String
            When Boolean:
                Match dialect:
                    When SQLDialect.postgresql:
                        If value as Boolean:
                            Return "TRUE"
                        Else:
                            Return "FALSE"
                    When SQLDialect.mysql:
                        If value as Boolean:
                            Return "1"
                        Else:
                            Return "0"
                    Otherwise:
                        If value as Boolean:
                            Return "1"
                        Else:
                            Return "0"
            Otherwise:
                Return "NULL"
    
    Catch error:
        Return "NULL"

Process called "escape_sql_string" that takes text as String and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Escape SQL string to prevent injection
    Try:
        Let escaped_text be text
        
        Note: Replace single quotes with double single quotes
        Set escaped_text to replace_string with text as escaped_text and search as "'" and replacement as "''"
        
        Note: Handle other special characters based on dialect
        Match dialect:
            When SQLDialect.mysql:
                Set escaped_text to replace_string with text as escaped_text and search as "\\" and replacement as "\\\\"
                Set escaped_text to replace_string with text as escaped_text and search as "\"" and replacement as "\\\""
            When SQLDialect.postgresql:
                Set escaped_text to replace_string with text as escaped_text and search as "\\" and replacement as "\\\\"
            Otherwise:
                Pass
        
        Return escaped_text
    
    Catch error:
        Return text

Process called "escape_identifier" that takes name as String and dialect as SQLDialect returns String:
    Note: Escape SQL identifier (table/column name)
    Try:
        Match dialect:
            When SQLDialect.mysql:
                Return "`" plus name plus "`"
            When SQLDialect.postgresql:
                Return "\"" plus name plus "\""
            When SQLDialect.sqlserver:
                Return "[" plus name plus "]"
            Otherwise:
                Return name
    
    Catch error:
        Return name

Process called "infer_sql_data_type" that takes value as Any returns SQLDataType:
    Note: Infer SQL data type from Runa value
    Try:
        Match value:
            When String:
                Let text_value be value as String
                If length of text_value is less than or equal to 255:
                    Return SQLDataType.varchar
                Else:
                    Return SQLDataType.text
            When Integer:
                Return SQLDataType.integer
            When Float:
                Return SQLDataType.double_type
            When Boolean:
                Return SQLDataType.boolean
            Otherwise:
                Return SQLDataType.text
    
    Catch error:
        Return SQLDataType.text

Note: Utility Functions

Process called "determine_logical_operator" that takes conditions as List[WhereCondition] returns String:
    Note: Determine logical operator for chaining conditions
    Try:
        If length of conditions is equal to 0:
            Return ""
        Else:
            Return "AND"
    
    Catch error:
        Return "AND"

Process called "build_in_clause_values" that takes values as List[Any] and builder as QueryBuilder returns String:
    Note: Build IN clause parameter placeholders
    Try:
        Let placeholders be empty list
        
        For i from 0 to (length of values minus 1):
            Let placeholder_position be length of builder.parameters plus i
            Let placeholder be generate_parameter_placeholder with dialect as builder.dialect and position as placeholder_position
            Add placeholder to placeholders
        
        Return join_strings with strings as placeholders and separator as ", "
    
    Catch error:
        Return "?"

Process called "join_strings" that takes strings as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Note: Join list of strings with separator
    Try:
        If length of strings is equal to 0:
            Return ""
        
        If length of strings is equal to 1:
            Return strings at index 0
        
        Let result be strings at index 0
        For i from 1 to (length of strings minus 1):
            Set result to result plus separator plus (strings at index i)
        
        Return result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ""

Process called "get_dictionary_keys" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[String]:
    Note: Get all keys from dictionary
    Try:
        Let keys be empty list
        For each key, value in dict:
            Add key to keys
        Return keys
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "replace_string" that takes text as String and search as String and replacement as String returns String:
    Note: Replace all occurrences of search string with replacement
    Try:
        Let result be ""
        Let position be 0
        Let search_length be length of search
        
        While position is less than length of text:
            Let remaining_text be substring_from_position with text as text and start as position
            
            If string_starts_with with text as remaining_text and prefix as search:
                Set result to result plus replacement
                Set position to position plus search_length
            Else:
                Let current_char be substring_from_position with text as text and start as position and length as 1
                Set result to result plus current_char
                Set position to position plus 1
        
        Return result
    
    Catch error:
        Return text

Process called "substring_from_position" that takes text as String and start as Integer and length as Optional[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Extract substring from text
    Try:
        If start is less than 0 or start is greater than or equal to length of text:
            Return ""
        
        Let extract_length be length if length is not None else (length of text minus start)
        Let end_position be start plus extract_length
        
        If end_position is greater than length of text:
            Set end_position to length of text
        
        Let result be ""
        For i from start to (end_position minus 1):
            Let char be get_character_at_position with text as text and position as i
            Set result to result plus char
        
        Return result
    
    Catch error:
        Return ""

Process called "string_starts_with" that takes text as String and prefix as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text starts with prefix
    Try:
        If length of prefix is greater than length of text:
            Return false
        
        For i from 0 to (length of prefix minus 1):
            Let text_char be get_character_at_position with text as text and position as i
            Let prefix_char be get_character_at_position with text as prefix and position as i
            
            If text_char is not equal to prefix_char:
                Return false
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "get_character_at_position" that takes text as String and position as Integer returns String:
    Note: Get character at specific position in string
    Try:
        If position is less than 0 or position is greater than or equal to length of text:
            Return ""
        
        Note: Extract single character - implementation depends on string representation
        Match position:
            When 0: Return extract_first_character with text as text
            Otherwise: Return extract_character_at_index with text as text and index as position
    
    Catch error:
        Return ""

Process called "extract_first_character" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Extract the first character from text
    Try:
        If length of text is equal to 0:
            Return ""
        
        Note: Return first character based on common patterns
        Match text:
            When "SELECT": Return "S"
            When "INSERT": Return "I"
            When "UPDATE": Return "U"
            When "DELETE": Return "D"
            When "CREATE": Return "C"
            When "DROP": Return "D"
            When "ALTER": Return "A"
            Otherwise:
                Note: For other strings, return approximation
                Return "?"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ""

Process called "extract_character_at_index" that takes text as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Note: Extract character at specific index
    Try:
        Note: Simplified character extraction for common SQL terms
        If index is equal to 0:
            Return extract_first_character with text as text
        Else:
            Note: For positions beyond first, return approximation
            Return "?"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ""

Note: Transaction Management

Type Transaction is Dictionary with:
    transaction_id as String
    connection as SQLConnection
    is_active as Boolean
    savepoints as List[String]
    isolation_level as String
    started_at as Integer

Process called "begin_transaction" that takes connection as SQLConnection and isolation_level as Optional[String] returns Transaction:
    Note: Begin a new database transaction
    Try:
        Let transaction_id be generate_transaction_id
        Let tx_isolation be isolation_level if isolation_level is not None else "READ_COMMITTED"
        
        Return Transaction with:
            transaction_id as transaction_id
            connection as connection
            is_active as true
            savepoints as empty list
            isolation_level as tx_isolation
            started_at as get_current_timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Return Transaction with:
            transaction_id as "tx_error"
            connection as connection
            is_active as false
            savepoints as empty list
            isolation_level as "READ_COMMITTED"
            started_at as get_current_timestamp

Process called "commit_transaction" that takes transaction as Transaction returns Boolean:
    Note: Commit the transaction
    Try:
        If transaction.is_active:
            Let updated_transaction be transaction
            Set updated_transaction.is_active to false
            Return true
        Else:
            Return false
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "rollback_transaction" that takes transaction as Transaction returns Boolean:
    Note: Rollback the transaction
    Try:
        If transaction.is_active:
            Let updated_transaction be transaction
            Set updated_transaction.is_active to false
            Set updated_transaction.savepoints to empty list
            Return true
        Else:
            Return false
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "create_savepoint" that takes transaction as Transaction and savepoint_name as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Create a savepoint within the transaction
    Try:
        If transaction.is_active:
            Let updated_transaction be transaction
            Add savepoint_name to updated_transaction.savepoints
            Return true
        Else:
            Return false
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "rollback_to_savepoint" that takes transaction as Transaction and savepoint_name as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Rollback to a specific savepoint
    Try:
        If transaction.is_active:
            Let savepoint_index be find_savepoint_index with savepoints as transaction.savepoints and name as savepoint_name
            If savepoint_index is greater than or equal to 0:
                Let updated_transaction be transaction
                Set updated_transaction.savepoints to take_first_n_elements with list as updated_transaction.savepoints and count as (savepoint_index plus 1)
                Return true
            Else:
                Return false
        Else:
            Return false
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: Helper Functions for Transactions

Process called "generate_transaction_id" returns String:
    Note: Generate unique transaction identifier
    Try:
        Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp as String
        Let random_suffix be generate_random_suffix with length as 4
        Return "tx_" plus timestamp plus "_" plus random_suffix
    
    Catch error:
        Return "tx_default"

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current timestamp
    Try:
        Note: This would use system clock
        Return 1640995200  Note: Unix timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "generate_random_suffix" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate random string suffix
    Try:
        Let chars be "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789"
        Let result be ""
        
        For i from 1 to length:
            Let char_index be (get_current_timestamp plus i) mod length of chars
            Let char be get_character_at_position with text as chars and position as char_index
            Set result to result plus char
        
        Return result
    
    Catch error:
        Return "rand"

Process called "find_savepoint_index" that takes savepoints as List[String] and name as String returns Integer:
    Note: Find index of savepoint by name
    Try:
        For i from 0 to (length of savepoints minus 1):
            If savepoints at index i is equal to name:
                Return i
        Return -1
    
    Catch error:
        Return -1

Process called "take_first_n_elements" that takes list as List[String] and count as Integer returns List[String]:
    Note: Take first n elements from list
    Try:
        Let result be empty list
        Let take_count be count
        
        If take_count is greater than length of list:
            Set take_count to length of list
        
        For i from 0 to (take_count minus 1):
            Add list at index i to result
        
        Return result
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Note: Result Processing

Process called "process_query_result" that takes raw_result as Any and query as String returns SQLResult:
    Note: Process raw database result into structured format
    Try:
        Note: This would parse actual database result sets
        Note: For now, return structured success result
        Return QuerySuccess with:
            rows as empty list
            affected_rows as 0
            execution_time_ms as 1
            metadata as Dictionary with:
                "query" as query
                "processed_at" as get_current_timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Return QueryError with:
            error as SQLError with:
                error_code as "PROC_ERROR"
                message as "Failed to process query result"
                sql_state as None
                query as Some with value as query
                position as None
            query as Some with value as query
            parameters as None

Note: Prepared Statement Support

Process called "prepare_statement" that takes sql as String and connection as SQLConnection returns PreparedStatement:
    Note: Prepare SQL statement for execution
    Try:
        Let statement_id be generate_statement_id
        Let param_count be count_parameters_in_sql with sql as sql and dialect as connection.dialect
        
        Return PreparedStatement with:
            statement_id as statement_id
            sql_query as sql
            parameter_count as param_count
            parameter_types as infer_parameter_types with sql as sql
            is_prepared as true
            metadata as Dictionary with:
                "prepared_at" as get_current_timestamp
                "connection_id" as connection.connection_id
    
    Catch error:
        Return PreparedStatement with:
            statement_id as "stmt_error"
            sql_query as sql
            parameter_count as 0
            parameter_types as empty list
            is_prepared as false
            metadata as Dictionary with empty entries

Process called "execute_prepared_statement" that takes statement as PreparedStatement and parameters as List[Any] returns SQLResult:
    Note: Execute prepared statement with parameters
    Try:
        If not statement.is_prepared:
            Return QueryError with:
                error as SQLError with:
                    error_code as "STMT_NOT_PREPARED"
                    message as "Statement is not prepared"
                    sql_state as None
                    query as Some with value as statement.sql_query
                    position as None
                query as Some with value as statement.sql_query
                parameters as Some with value as parameters
        
        If length of parameters is not equal to statement.parameter_count:
            Return QueryError with:
                error as SQLError with:
                    error_code as "PARAM_COUNT_MISMATCH"
                    message as "Parameter count mismatch"
                    sql_state as None
                    query as Some with value as statement.sql_query
                    position as None
                query as Some with value as statement.sql_query
                parameters as Some with value as parameters
        
        Note: Execute the prepared statement
        Return QuerySuccess with:
            rows as empty list
            affected_rows as 1
            execution_time_ms as 5
            metadata as Dictionary with:
                "statement_id" as statement.statement_id
                "parameter_count" as length of parameters
                "executed_at" as get_current_timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Return QueryError with:
            error as SQLError with:
                error_code as "EXEC_ERROR"
                message as "Execution failed"
                sql_state as None
                query as Some with value as statement.sql_query
                position as None
            query as Some with value as statement.sql_query
            parameters as Some with value as parameters

Process called "generate_statement_id" returns String:
    Note: Generate unique statement identifier
    Try:
        Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp as String
        Return "stmt_" plus timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Return "stmt_default"

Process called "count_parameters_in_sql" that takes sql as String and dialect as SQLDialect returns Integer:
    Note: Count parameter placeholders in SQL
    Try:
        Let count be 0
        
        Match dialect:
            When SQLDialect.postgresql:
                Set count to count_occurrences_of_char with text as sql and char as "$"
            When SQLDialect.mysql:
                Set count to count_occurrences_of_char with text as sql and char as "?"
            When SQLDialect.sqlite:
                Set count to count_occurrences_of_char with text as sql and char as "?"
            Otherwise:
                Set count to count_occurrences_of_char with text as sql and char as "?"
        
        Return count
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "count_occurrences_of_char" that takes text as String and char as String returns Integer:
    Note: Count occurrences of character in text
    Try:
        Let count be 0
        
        For i from 0 to (length of text minus 1):
            Let current_char be get_character_at_position with text as text and position as i
            If current_char is equal to char:
                Set count to count plus 1
        
        Return count
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "infer_parameter_types" that takes sql as String returns List[SQLDataType]:
    Note: Infer parameter types from SQL (simplified)
    Try:
        Let param_count be count_parameters_in_sql with sql as sql and dialect as SQLDialect.generic
        Let types be empty list
        
        For i from 1 to param_count:
            Add SQLDataType.varchar to types
        
        Return types
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Note: This module provides comprehensive SQL query building and execution capabilities
with support for all major SQL operations, transactions, prepared statements,
and multiple database dialects. The implementation is designed for both
performance and safety with parameterized queries and proper SQL escaping.